Package contextualegonetwork

Class Node

  • java.lang.Object
    • contextualegonetwork.Node
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    Person, SmartObject
    class Node
extends java.lang.Object
    This class implements a node in the Social Graph, which is representative of a node in a particular layer of the HSG. Nodes are mapped in-between layers through a mapping function, for which two nodes in different layers correspond to each other if they have the identifier

      • addEdgeInteraction

        public int addEdgeInteraction​(Node src,
                              Node dst,
                              long timestamp,
                              int duration,
                              java.lang.String type)
        Adds an interaction on an edge of this node. The edge is identified by its source and destination. This node needs to be either the source or the destination of the edge.
        Parameters:
        src - The source node of the edge
        dst - The destination node of the edge
        timestamp - The timestamp of when the interaction started
        duration - The duration of the interaction
        type - The type of the interaction
        Returns:
        -1 if neither the source nor the destination of the edge is this node, -2 if the edge having this node as source or destination doesn't exist, 0 if the operation was successful
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if src, dst or type are null
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if timestamp is less than 0 or duration is less than 0 or type is an empty string

      • addEdgeInteraction

                              long timestamp,

                              java.lang.String type)

        duration - The duration of the interaction
        type - The type of the interaction
